gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Rockets 135, Raptors 106
gameRecap.excerpt: The Rockets defeat the Raptors, 135-106. Cam Whitmore (career-high 25 points, six rebounds) and Amen Thompson (career-high 19 points, seven rebounds, four assists) led Houston while Alperen Sengun had a great performance with 24 points, 13 rebounds, and eight assists. Scottie Barnes led the Raptors with 28 points, seven rebounds, and four assists as Immanuel Quickley added 25 points and a season-high six 3PT FGs. Houston moves to 23-25 as the Raptors move to 17-31.
